text: @FedExHelp ... is now "PENDING." I'm left with a choice to either patch up the broken part so that the car can limp out on Monday, then tear it all down and reassemble it again when the part *does* arrive, or arrange substitute transportation at additional expense

@FedExHelp My plan was to disassemble the engine today, receive the part by the evening, and then put everything back together tomorrow so the car would be drive-able for Monday morning. Unfortunately, it's the end of the day, the package hasn't arrived, and the scheduled date

@FedExHelp I was expecting a car part from @ipdVolvo via @FedEx Home Delivery on 9/25, end-of-day. Then @FedEx sent me an alert saying that the delivery date was changed to 9/22, end-of-day. I moved my repair plans up to today based on this expectation.

@FedExHelp ...until such time as the part arrives and I can make time to finish the job. I'm not sure there's really a way you can help me, other than to listen to my complaint, and maybe consider not telling people packages are going to arrive on days that they are not.

@prwood Hello Peter, my name is Karin. I apologize for the inconvenience this has caused, I would be happy to look into this matter. Please DM the tracking number, delivery address and contact information. Thank you!
